<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1451,700,907]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
As currently known, this is a locally restricted endemic, known from only a handful of collections, all of them from adjacent localities at the northern end of the Serranía de Huanchaca around 
<geoCoordinate box="[987,1079,773,799]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" precision="925" value="-13.65">13°39´S</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[1134,1237,772,799]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" precision="925" value="-60.833332">60°50´W</geoCoordinate>
at 200–400 (–850) m., 
<emphasis box="[179,395,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Peña &amp; Foster 223</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[410,510,809,835]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">holotype</typeStatus>
NY photo!; isotype 
<collectionCode box="[739,801,809,835]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15753" name="Museo de Historia Natural Noel Kempff Mercado -- Universidad Aut�noma Gabriel Ren� Moreno" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">USZ</collectionCode>
!); 
<emphasis box="[826,1044,808,835]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Gutierrez et al. 888</emphasis>
(K!, 
<collectionCode box="[1105,1167,809,835]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15753" name="Museo de Historia Natural Noel Kempff Mercado -- Universidad Aut�noma Gabriel Ren� Moreno" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">USZ</collectionCode>
!); 
<emphasis box="[1191,1398,808,835]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Killeen et al. 5412</emphasis>
(K!, 
<collectionCode box="[136,198,845,871]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15753" name="Museo de Historia Natural Noel Kempff Mercado -- Universidad Aut�noma Gabriel Ren� Moreno" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">USZ</collectionCode>
!). A distinctive species with a large exserted efoliate panicle of globose capitula and whole plant densely hispid with 
<quantity box="[193,279,881,907]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4mm</quantity>
setae. One of three Huanchaca endemics along with 
<emphasis box="[872,1010,880,906]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">M. suberosa</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1193,881,906]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="rastrera">
<emphasis box="[1064,1193,881,906]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
M. 
